%% 13.3 Ruffing after first leading trumps
QX|13B03,RUFFING AFTER FIRST LEADING TRUMPS|
HT|d|Va|4|cs|1|cp|4|fp||
at|
^-{    RUFFING AFTER FIRST LEADING TRUMPS    }
^-|
cp||fp||at|^B@2^Y@3T|FP||AT|he lead of trumps by the Declarer need not always be postponed in order to realize fully any available ruffing power. Sometimes the Dummy is so long in trumps that the short suit need not be attacked first. Trumps can be drawn first of all without losing any ruffing power, which may be utilized later.|
PG| ***** 62 ***** |


AT|

This situation arises, usually, when the Dummy holds four trumps. Generally speaking, when the Dummy contains only three trumps, the drawing of trumps must be deferred until the Declarer has taken whatever he needs in ruffing-tricks. With four trumps in the Dummy, the Declarer may usually lead one round of trumps with complete safety. You must, of course, always notice how many losers you must dispose of in your hand, and how many trumps the Dummy has available for ruffing purposes.|
PG| ***** 63 ***** |


AT|

